\int_0^\infty e^{-x^2} \sin{2xb}\, dx =e^{-b^2}\int_0^b e^{x^2} \, dx, \, b>0, 
 0=\int_0^a e^{-x^2} \, dx + \int_0^b e^{-(a+iy)^2} i \, dy + \int_a^0 e^{-(x+ib)^2} \, dx + \int_b^0 e^{-(-a+iy)^2} i \, dy
= \int_0^a e^{-x^2} \, dx - \int_0^b e^{(-a^2-y^2-2ayi)} i \, dy +  \int_a^0 e^{(-x^2-2xbi+b^2)} \, dx +  \int_b^0 e^{(-a^2+y^2+2ayi)}i \, dy 
 =  \int_0^a e^{-x^2} \, dx -e^{b^2} \int_0^a e^{-x^2} (\cos{(-2bx)}+i\sin{(-2bx)}) \, dx + \left[  -ie^{-a^2}\int_0^b e^{y^2} (e^{2iay}- e^{-2iay} \, dy \right]
 =  \int_0^a e^{-x^2} \, dx -e^{b^2} \int_0^a e^{-x^2} (\cos{(2bx)}-i\sin{(2bx)}) \, dx + \left[  -ie^{-a^2}\int_0^b e^{y^2} (e^{2iay}- e^{-2iay}) \, dy \right]
= \int_0^a e^{-x^2} \, dx -e^{b^2} \int_0^a e^{-x^2} (\cos{(2bx)}-i\sin{(2bx)}) \, dx + 2e^{-a^2}\int_0^b e^{y^2}\sin(2ay) \, dy  
